@parties
go-to: menu

**PTB** - *Partido Trabalhista Brasileiro* (Brazilian Labor Party) - this is us. We are a pro-union, nationalist and social-democratic party formed by Getúlio Vargas in 1945. We are one of the major defenders of the Constitution and almost none of our members supported the military veto against Goulart.

**PSD** - *Partido Social Democrático* (Social Democratic Party) - a centrist party also formed by Vargas and several of governors of the Estado Novo period. It goes wherever is needed, adopting a plethora of ideological faces. It is the party of Juscelino Kubitschek and Tancredo Neves and a usually an ally of ours.

Current relations: [+ psd_relation : relationships +]

**UDN** - *União Democrática Nacional* (National Democratic Union) - a center-right to right-wing party dead-set on the destruction of Getulism as an ideology. It emerged as one of the main figures against Vargas during the Estado Novo regime and continued to resist any attempts by the PSD or the PTB to gain power. Its main face is Carlos Lacerda.

Current relations: [+ udn_relation : relationships +]

**PSP** - *Partido Social Progressista* (Social Progressive Party) - a populist conservative party founded by former São Paulo governor Adhemar de Barros. It has supported Vargas, even giving him 
a vice-president. 

Current relations: [+ psp_relation : relationships +]

**PDC** - *Partido Democrata Cristão* (Christian Democratic Party) - a centrist to center-right Christian party supported by the urban middle class. Its centrist faction is usually the one in control of party politics.

Current relations: [+ pdc_relation  : relationships +]

**PTN** - *Partido Trabalhista Nacional* (National Labor Party) - a minor conservative party formed by former members of Dutra's labor ministry. It has seen limited success, with its only major achievement being the election of Jânio Quadros. 

Current relations: [+ ptn_relation : relationships +]

**PRP** - *Partido de Representação Popular* - (Popular Representation Party, or Integralists) - a far-right nationalist and integralist party. Although it was mostly relevant during the Estado Novo period, it still maintains a small presence in Congress.

Current relations: [+ prp_relation : relationships +]

**Other parties** - there is a multitude of small parties. such as the Brazilian Socialist Party, the Social Labor Party, the Republican Party and others. They usually stay between the PTB and the UDN.

