@factions

**Internal factions of the PTB**

Overall dissent: [+ dissent_percent : dissent +]

**Getulists**

They are the bureaucrats, the trade unionists from the official corporatism, and professional politicians linked to Vargas. All of them are against any type of class conflict, opting instead for a orderly society under the teachings of Vargas.

Strength: [+ varguist_strength : strength +]

Dissent: [+ varguist_dissent : dissent +]

**Labourists**

Liberals and social-democratic elements of the intellectual wing of the party. Fierce defenders of “evolutionary socialism” (a gradual transition to socialism), they are one of the main opponents of the Getulist faction.

Strength: [+ labor_strength : strength +]

Dissent: [+ labor_dissent : dissent +]

**Reformists**

A faction which finds themselves as a marriage between the Labourists and the Getulists. Trying to consolidate the party in state institutions and to turn it into an agent and facilitator of popular mobilization among workers, with a reformist and nationalist policy.

Strength: [+ reformist_strength : strength +]

Dissent: [+ reformist_dissent : dissent +]

**Unaligned**

While they are not identified with any faction, the unaligned movement is one of the most important groups in the party. 

Strength: [+ unaligned_strength : strength +]

Dissent: [+ unaligned_dissent : dissent +]

